title: For Sale:  Krag Model 1898 .30-40
postcontent: This beautiful Krag-Jorgenson Model 1898 is for sale. It has the original inspection cartouche "JSA 1899" and an additional unit cartouche "5th/1/E" The unit cartouche, combined with the inspection date leads me to believe this rifle was carried by the 5th Infantry Regiment 1st Army Company E. The 5th Regiment served in the Philippine-American War in 1900 (well within the possible date range of this rifle) and earned one combat streamer for its service there. It is highly possible given these circumstances this rifle was involved in the effort to "Civilize them with a Krag!" This rifle represents both America's leaving the Monroe Doctrine behind and the beginnings of Her global superpower status. Serial No. 241444. bore is clean, action is smooth, absurd side magazine chambers rounds gracefully. The rifle is missing the rear sight but these can be easily aquired on Ebay for less than $45. Furthermore, given the US Army's policy of continuously updating the rear sight, I feel the overall value of the piece is not effected.Let me know if you would like to see more pictures. The Echo Trigger is a ground breaking drop in design that is approved by the ATF. The Echo Trigger allows the shooter to select from 3 different settings. Safe Mode: Firearm will not fire. This ammunition is manufactured in the USA using .308 diameter Flat Point heavy poly-metal coated ultra-hard lead-antimony core projectiles.These bullets are precision die cast with the top quality alloy followed by a thick polymer coating and a full resizing to ensure top accuracy and quality.
